  "prompt": "Why does my vagina smell fishy after intercourse and a man has ejaculated inside me?",
  "response": "A fishy smell after intercourse, especially following ejaculation, may be due to several factors, including bacterial vaginosis (BV). BV is a common vaginal infection caused by an imbalance of naturally occurring bacterial flora. Semen can alter the vaginal pH, potentially exacerbating this imbalance.\n\nOther possibilities might include a reaction to personal hygiene products, lubricants, or latex if using condoms. It's also important to consider overall hygiene and any recent changes in sexual or personal care practices.\n\nIf you experience persistent symptoms such as unusual discharge, itching, or irritation along with the smell, it is advisable to consult a healthcare professional for a proper diagnosis and appropriate treatment. They can rule out any infections and provide guidance on maintaining a healthy vaginal environment.",
